HEADWORD: Crab-yaws
<hw>Crab"-yaws`</hw> <pr>(kr?b"y?z`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A disease in the West Indies. It is a kind of
ulcer on the soles of the feet, with very hard edges. See
<er>Yaws</er>.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crache</ent>⟦br⟧
